Question: Explain to a child how to do a task (e.g., cross the street).
Answer:
Crossing a street is very dangerous. There are a lot of cars going very fast, and you need to be careful to not get hit by one. To do that, you need to look to both sides of the street a couple times before you decide to cross. First look to your left, then to your right, and again to your left. If there are no cars, you may cross.